1
00:01:09,459 --> 00:01:11,495
Sometimes, I think I'm cursed.

2
00:01:11,670 --> 00:01:14,457
Because of something that happened
before I was even born.

3
00:01:15,465 --> 00:01:18,502
See, a long time ago,
there was this family.

4
00:01:19,845 --> 00:01:21,710
The papa, he was a musician.

5
00:01:22,723 --> 00:01:26,341
He and his family would sing
and dance and count their blessings.

6
00:01:27,686 --> 00:01:31,395
But he also had a dream.
To play for the world.

7
00:01:34,401 --> 00:01:40,362
And one day, he left with his guitar
and never returned.

8
00:01:49,041 --> 00:01:50,406
And the mamé...

9
00:01:50,751 --> 00:01:53,333
She didn't have time to cry
over that walk—away musician.

10
00:01:55,922 --> 00:02:00,666
After banishing all music from her life
she found a way...

11
00:02:00,844 --> 00:02:02,254
to provide for her daughter.

12
00:02:06,391 --> 00:02:09,599
She rolled up her sleeves
and she learned to make shoes.

13
00:02:14,941 --> 00:02:20,277
She could have made candy,
or ﬁreworks, or sparkly unden/vear...

14
00:02:20,447 --> 00:02:25,407
for wrestlers, but no, she chose shoes.

15
00:02:28,246 --> 00:02:30,282
Then she taught her daughter
to make shoes.

16
00:02:31,875 --> 00:02:34,207
And later, she taught her son—in—law.

17
00:02:35,587 --> 00:02:37,452
Then her grandkids got roped in.

18
00:02:39,132 --> 00:02:41,794
As her family grew,
so did the business.

19
00:02:43,595 --> 00:02:46,132
Music had torn her family apart.

20
00:02:47,224 --> 00:02:49,260
But shoes held them all together.

21
00:02:51,144 --> 00:02:55,137
You see, that woman was my great-
great—grandmother, Mamé Imelda.

22
00:02:56,483 --> 00:02:58,769
She died way before I was born.

23
00:02:59,319 --> 00:03:03,813
But my family still tells her story
every year on Dia de los Muertos...

24
00:03:03,990 --> 00:03:05,321
the Day of the Dead.

25
00:03:05,450 --> 00:03:09,489
And her little girl, she's my
great—grandmother, Mamé Coco.

26
00:03:10,664 --> 00:03:11,949
Hola, Mama’ Coco.

27
00:03:12,499 --> 00:03:14,660
How are you, Julio?

28
00:03:14,751 --> 00:03:16,992
Actually, my name is Miguel.

29
00:03:17,129 --> 00:03:20,747
Mama Coco has trouble
remembering things.

30
00:03:20,924 --> 00:03:24,917
But it's good to talk to her anyway.
So, I tell her pretty much everything.

31
00:03:25,137 --> 00:03:29,221
I used to run like this. But now
I run like this which is way faster.

32
00:03:29,433 --> 00:03:32,675
And the winner is Luchadora Coco!

33
00:03:33,937 --> 00:03:36,098
I have a dimple on this side,
but not on this side.

34
00:03:36,189 --> 00:03:38,054
Dimple, no dimple. Dimple, no dimple.

35
00:03:38,150 --> 00:03:40,266
Miguel, eat your food.

36
00:03:40,444 --> 00:03:42,810
My abuelita, she's
Mama Coco's daughter.

37
00:03:42,988 --> 00:03:45,980
Oh, you're a twig, mijo.
Have some more.

38
00:03:46,158 --> 00:03:47,147
No, gracias.

39
00:03:47,325 --> 00:03:50,442
I asked if you would like more tamalesl

40
00:03:50,620 --> 00:03:51,655
Si?

41
00:03:51,830 --> 00:03:54,162
That's what I thought you said!

42
00:03:54,291 --> 00:03:57,624
Abuelita runs our house
just like Mama Imelda did.

43
00:04:00,672 --> 00:04:01,627
No music!

44
00:04:03,216 --> 00:04:04,331
No music!

45
00:04:04,509 --> 00:04:07,626
-Y aunque la vida
-No music!

46
00:04:07,971 --> 00:04:11,259
I think we're the only family in México
who hates music.

47
00:04:11,975 --> 00:04:14,808
And my family's ﬁne with that. But me...

48
00:04:14,978 --> 00:04:17,060
-Be back by lunch, mijo.
—Love you, Mama.

49
00:04:18,398 --> 00:04:20,730
I am not like the rest of my family!

50
00:04:21,943 --> 00:04:23,399
-Hola, Miguel!
-Hola!

51
00:04:29,409 --> 00:04:31,570
-Muchas gracias.
-De nada, Miguel.

52
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:37,990
Hey! Dante!

53
00:04:39,503 --> 00:04:43,212
Sit. Down. Roll over. Shake.

54
00:04:44,257 --> 00:04:45,167
Fist bump!

55
00:04:45,342 --> 00:04:47,207
Good boy, Dante!

56
00:04:51,181 --> 00:04:53,672
I know I'm not supposed to love music.

57
00:04:53,850 --> 00:04:57,183
But it's not my fault! It's his!

58
00:04:57,354 --> 00:05:01,939
Ernesto de la Cruz.
The greatest musician of all time.

59
00:05:02,108 --> 00:05:07,603
Right here in this very plaza,
Ernesto de la Cruz took his first steps...

60
00:05:07,781 --> 00:05:11,148
toward becoming the most beloved
singer in Mexican history.

61
00:05:11,910 --> 00:05:15,778
He started out a total nobody
from Santa Cecilia, like me.

62
00:05:17,123 --> 00:05:20,957
But when he played music,
he made people fall in love with him.

63
00:05:21,878 --> 00:05:23,618
He starred in movies.

64
00:05:24,297 --> 00:05:27,960
He had the coolest guitar! He could ﬂy!

65
00:05:28,510 --> 00:05:30,842
And he wrote the best songs.

66
00:05:30,929 --> 00:05:32,794
But my all—time favorite, it's...

67
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:36,632
-Remember me
-Remember me

68
00:05:36,810 --> 00:05:38,471
Though I have to say goodbye

69
00:05:38,603 --> 00:05:40,264
-Remember me
-Remember me

70
00:05:40,438 --> 00:05:44,147
Don't let it make you cry
For even if I'm far away

71
00:05:44,317 --> 00:05:45,978
I hold you in my heart
I sing a secret song to you

72
00:05:47,946 --> 00:05:50,779
Each night we are apart
Remember me

73
00:05:50,949 --> 00:05:52,905
Though I have to travel far

74
00:05:52,993 --> 00:05:54,654
-Remember me
-Remember me

75
00:05:54,828 --> 00:05:56,989
Each time you hear a sad guitar

76
00:05:57,122 --> 00:06:01,286
Know that I'm with you
the only way that I can be

77
00:06:01,793 --> 00:06:05,331
Until you're in my arms again

78
00:06:05,505 --> 00:06:07,496
He lived the kind of life
you dream about.

79
00:06:12,095 --> 00:06:13,676
Until 1942.

80
00:06:15,682 --> 00:06:18,719
When he was crushed by a giant bell.

81
00:06:19,686 --> 00:06:22,098
I want to be just like him.

82
00:06:28,278 --> 00:06:33,944
Sometimes, I look at de la Cruz and
I get this feeling like we're connected.

83
00:06:34,826 --> 00:06:39,365
Like if he could play music,
maybe someday, I could too.

84
00:06:40,373 --> 00:06:42,204
If it wasn't for my family.

85
00:06:42,334 --> 00:06:44,666
-Ay-ay-ay, muchacho.
-Huh?

86
00:06:44,836 --> 00:06:46,952
I asked for a shoe shine
not your life story.

87
00:06:47,130 --> 00:06:48,540
Oh, yeah. Sorry.

88
00:06:49,215 --> 00:06:52,378
I just can't really talk about
any of this at home. So...

89
00:06:52,552 --> 00:06:55,544
If I were you, I'd march
right up to my family and say...

90
00:06:55,722 --> 00:06:58,054
"Hey, I'm a musician. Deal with it."

91
00:06:58,224 --> 00:07:01,591
—I could never say that.
—You are a musician, no?

92
00:07:02,062 --> 00:07:05,554
I don't know.
I mean, I only really play for myself.

93
00:07:06,149 --> 00:07:10,563
Did de la Cruz become the world's
best musician by hiding his skills’?

94
00:07:10,737 --> 00:07:15,697
No! He walked out onto that plaza
and he played out loud.

95
00:07:15,867 --> 00:07:17,653
Mira, mira, they're
setting up for tonight!

96
00:07:18,203 --> 00:07:20,615
The music competition
for Dla de Muertos.

97
00:07:20,747 --> 00:07:23,238
You want to be like your hero?
You should sign up!

98
00:07:23,416 --> 00:07:25,657
Uh—uh. My family would freak!

99
00:07:26,252 --> 00:07:29,710
Look, if you're too scared
then, well, have fun making shoes.

100
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:33,331
Come on, what did
de la Cruz always say?

101
00:07:33,927 --> 00:07:35,417
Seize your moment?

102
00:07:36,888 --> 00:07:38,674
Show me what you got, muchacho.

103
00:07:40,266 --> 00:07:41,847
I'll be your first audience.

104
00:07:49,275 --> 00:07:50,105
Miguel!

105
00:07:52,195 --> 00:07:53,605
-Abuelita!
—What are you doing here?

106
00:07:56,116 --> 00:07:57,731
You leave my grandson alone.

107
00:07:57,867 --> 00:07:59,823
Doﬁa, please! Iwasjust getting a shine.

108
00:07:59,911 --> 00:08:03,028
I know your tricks, mariachi.
What did he say to you?

109
00:08:03,123 --> 00:08:04,659
He was just showing me his guitar.

110
00:08:04,749 --> 00:08:05,909
Shame on you.

111
00:08:06,668 --> 00:08:11,788
My grandson is a sweet little
angelito querido cielito.

112
00:08:13,049 --> 00:08:15,882
He wants no part of your music,
mariachi. You keep away from him.

113
00:08:19,389 --> 00:08:22,973
Ay, pobrecito. Oh, estas bien, mijo.

114
00:08:25,270 --> 00:08:27,386
You know better than to
be here in this place!

115
00:08:27,564 --> 00:08:30,647
You will come home. Now.

116
00:08:41,411 --> 00:08:44,995
How many times have we told you?
That plaza is crawling with mariachis.

117
00:08:45,081 --> 00:08:46,491
Yes, Tio Berto.

118
00:08:47,167 --> 00:08:50,125
-No, no, no, no, no!
—Go away, you. Go!

119
00:08:50,295 --> 00:08:51,455
It's just Dante.

120
00:08:51,629 --> 00:08:56,669
Never name a street dog. They'll follow
you forever. Now, go get my shoe.

121
00:09:02,807 --> 00:09:05,594
I found your son in Mariachi Plaza.

122
00:09:05,685 --> 00:09:06,925
AM Miguel!

123
00:09:07,020 --> 00:09:09,136
You know how Abuelita feels
about the plaza.

124
00:09:09,314 --> 00:09:12,021
-I was just shining shoes.
-A musician's shoes!

125
00:09:14,194 --> 00:09:16,185
But the plaza's where
all the foot traffic is.

126
00:09:16,362 --> 00:09:19,980
If Abuelita says no more plaza,
then no more plaza.

127
00:09:20,116 --> 00:09:22,198
-But what about tonight?
—What's tonight?

128
00:09:22,368 --> 00:09:26,828
Well, they're having this talent show.
And Ithought I might...

129
00:09:27,457 --> 00:09:29,948
—Sign up?
—well, maybe?

130
00:09:30,543 --> 00:09:33,250
You have to have talent
to be in a talent show.

131
00:09:33,338 --> 00:09:36,045
What are you gonna do? Shine shoes?

132
00:09:36,132 --> 00:09:37,793
It's Dla de los Muertos.

133
00:09:37,884 --> 00:09:41,047
No one's going anywhere.
Tonight is about family.

134
00:09:41,721 --> 00:09:44,007
Ofrenda room. Va’monos.

135
00:09:54,859 --> 00:09:56,520
Don't give me that look.

136
00:09:56,694 --> 00:09:59,356
Dia de los Muertos is
the one night of the year

137
00:09:59,531 --> 00:10:01,362
our ancestors can come visit us.

138
00:10:01,533 --> 00:10:05,526
We've put their photos on the ofrenda
so their spirits can cross over.

139
00:10:05,703 --> 00:10:07,489
That is very important.

140
00:10:07,622 --> 00:10:10,409
If we don't put them up,
they can't come.

141
00:10:10,583 --> 00:10:14,826
We made all this food, set out
the things they loved in life, mijo.

142
00:10:15,004 --> 00:10:18,087
All this work to bring
the family together.

143
00:10:18,216 --> 00:10:23,381
I don't want you sneaking off to who
knows where. Where are you going?

144
00:10:23,471 --> 00:10:24,506
I thought we were done.

145
00:10:24,597 --> 00:10:29,341
Ay, Dios mio. Being part of this family
means being here for this family.

146
00:10:29,435 --> 00:10:33,178
-I don't want to see you end up Iike--
-Like Mama’ Coco's papa’?

147
00:10:33,314 --> 00:10:36,351
Never mention that man!
He's better off forgotten.

148
00:10:36,442 --> 00:10:37,431
But you're the one who——

149
00:10:37,527 --> 00:10:38,642
I was just——

150
00:10:38,736 --> 00:10:40,021
But-- I--

151
00:10:40,113 --> 00:10:43,276
Papa? Papa is home?

152
00:10:43,366 --> 00:10:46,199
Mama’, calmese, calmese.

153
00:10:46,286 --> 00:10:47,696
Papa’ is coming home?

154
00:10:47,787 --> 00:10:51,120
No, Mama. It's okay. I'm here.

155
00:10:52,292 --> 00:10:53,873
Who are you?

156
00:10:55,461 --> 00:10:56,621
Rest, Mama.

157
00:10:57,547 --> 00:11:02,541
I'm hard on you because I care, Miguel.
Miguel? Miguel?

158
00:11:05,972 --> 00:11:07,803
What are we going to do with that boy?

159
00:11:09,559 --> 00:11:12,767
You're right. That's just what he needs.

160
00:11:37,253 --> 00:11:40,370
It's you. Get in here.
Come on, Dante. Hurry up!

161
00:11:41,966 --> 00:11:45,254
You're gonna get me in trouble, boy.
Someone could hear me.

162
00:11:50,183 --> 00:11:52,014
I wish someone wanted to hear me.

163
00:11:53,436 --> 00:11:56,223
Other than you. Ew. Okay.

164
00:11:58,691 --> 00:11:59,806
Perfecto!

165
00:12:33,434 --> 00:12:35,550
I have to sing. I have to play!

166
00:12:36,187 --> 00:12:40,476
The music, it's not just in me, it is me.

167
00:12:42,568 --> 00:12:45,355
When life gets me down,
I play my guitar.

168
00:12:46,656 --> 00:12:51,400
The rest of the world may follow
the rules, but I must follow my heart.

169
00:12:53,413 --> 00:12:56,405
You know that feeling
like there's a song in the air and...

170
00:12:56,582 --> 00:12:57,913
it's playing just for you?

171
00:13:01,921 --> 00:13:05,004
A feeling so close...

172
00:13:05,091 --> 00:13:09,960
you could reach out and touch it

173
00:13:10,054 --> 00:13:15,674
I never knew I could want
something so much, but it's true

174
00:13:17,020 --> 00:13:18,385
You must have faith, sister.

175
00:13:18,521 --> 00:13:20,887
Oh, but, Padre, he will never listen.

176
00:13:21,065 --> 00:13:22,726
He will listen. To music.

177
00:13:23,109 --> 00:13:29,105
Only a song, only a song
has the power to change a heart

178
00:13:33,536 --> 00:13:36,278
Never underestimate
the power of music.

179
00:13:40,877 --> 00:13:44,119
But my father,
he will never give his permission.

180
00:13:44,297 --> 00:13:45,912
I am done asking permission.

181
00:13:46,090 --> 00:13:48,877
When you see your moment,
you mustn't let it pass you by.

182
00:13:49,052 --> 00:13:50,792
You must seize it!

183
00:13:50,928 --> 00:13:54,887
Seﬁor de la Cruz, what did it take
for you to seize your moment?

184
00:13:56,809 --> 00:14:01,428
I had to have faith in my dream.
No one was going to hand it to me.

185
00:14:01,564 --> 00:14:03,771
It was up to me to reach for that dream.

186
00:14:03,941 --> 00:14:07,308
—Grab it tight and make it come true.
-...and make it come true.

187
00:14:12,075 --> 00:14:15,442
No more hiding, Dante.
I got to seize my moment!

188
00:14:16,829 --> 00:14:19,866
I'm gonna play in Mariachi Plaza
if it kills me.

189
00:14:23,336 --> 00:14:26,248
Dia de los Muertos has begun!

190
00:14:26,923 --> 00:14:30,086
No, no. We have to make a clear path.

191
00:14:30,259 --> 00:14:34,673
The petals guide our ancestors home.
We don't want their spirits to get lost.

192
00:14:34,847 --> 00:14:38,840
We want them to come and enjoy
all the food and drinks on the ofrenda.

193
00:14:40,353 --> 00:14:42,844
Mama! Where should we put this table?

194
00:14:43,022 --> 00:14:44,512
In the courtyard, mr'jos.

195
00:14:44,690 --> 00:14:47,807
-You want it down by the kitchen?
-SI. Next to the other one.

196
00:14:50,822 --> 00:14:53,814
—Get under! Get under!
-Miguel?

197
00:14:53,950 --> 00:14:57,317
Nothing! Mama, Papa. I--

198
00:14:57,453 --> 00:15:01,913
Miguel, your abuelita had
the most wonderful idea.

199
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:06,121
We've all decided.
It's time you joined us in the workshop!

200
00:15:06,212 --> 00:15:07,292
What?

201
00:15:07,380 --> 00:15:08,711
No more shining shoes.

202
00:15:08,798 --> 00:15:11,631
You'll be making them every day
after school.

203
00:15:11,717 --> 00:15:17,337
Oh! Our MigueIi—ti—ti—ti—to carrying on
the family tradition.

204
00:15:17,473 --> 00:15:22,433
And on Dia de los Muertos!
Your ancestors will be so proud.

205
00:15:22,562 --> 00:15:26,146
You'll craft huaraches
just like your Tia Victoria.

206
00:15:26,232 --> 00:15:28,894
And wingtips like your Papa Julio.

207
00:15:29,068 --> 00:15:31,400
But what if I'm no good
at making shoes?

208
00:15:31,487 --> 00:15:35,071
Ah, Miguel.
You have your family here to guide you.

209
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:40,034
You are a Rivera. And a Rivera is...

210
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:43,742
A shoemaker. Through and through.

211
00:15:43,875 --> 00:15:46,742
That's my boy! Berto!

212
00:15:46,919 --> 00:15:49,661
Break out the good stuff.
I want to make a toast.

213
00:15:59,765 --> 00:16:03,098
Dante! No, Dante. Stop!

214
00:16:13,779 --> 00:16:16,987
No, no, no, no, no! No.

215
00:16:28,961 --> 00:16:31,122
De la Cruz's guitar?

216
00:16:31,297 --> 00:16:34,460
Papa ? Papa?

217
00:16:35,801 --> 00:16:39,589
Mama Coco,
is your papa Ernesto de la Cruz?

218
00:16:39,764 --> 00:16:42,130
Papa! Papa!

219
00:16:53,861 --> 00:16:55,817
Papa! Papa! It's him!

220
00:16:55,947 --> 00:16:57,903
I know who my
great—great—grandfather was.

221
00:16:58,032 --> 00:16:59,647
Miguel, get down from there.

222
00:16:59,909 --> 00:17:02,696
Mama Coco's father was
Ernesto de la Cruz!

223
00:17:02,787 --> 00:17:06,496
—What are you talking about?
-I'm gonna be a musician!

224
00:17:08,084 --> 00:17:11,747
What is all this?
You keep secrets from your own family?

225
00:17:11,837 --> 00:17:13,668
It's all that time he spends in the plaza.

226
00:17:13,756 --> 00:17:16,623
—Fills his head with crazy fantasies.
—It's not a fantasy.

227
00:17:16,801 --> 00:17:20,635
That man was Ernesto de la Cruz!
The greatest musician of all time!

228
00:17:20,721 --> 00:17:22,507
We've never known anything
about this man!

229
00:17:22,598 --> 00:17:25,886
But whoever he was,
he still abandoned his family.

230
00:17:26,018 --> 00:17:27,633
This is no future for my son.

231
00:17:27,728 --> 00:17:30,310
But, Papa, you said
my family would guide me.

232
00:17:30,398 --> 00:17:32,810
Well, de la Cruz is my family.

233
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:34,356
I'm supposed to play music.

234
00:17:34,485 --> 00:17:38,603
Never! That man's music was a curse.
Iwill not allow it.

235
00:17:38,698 --> 00:17:40,359
—If you would just |et——
-Miguel...

236
00:17:40,533 --> 00:17:43,240
You will listen to your family.
No more music.

237
00:17:43,369 --> 00:17:46,532
—Just listen to me play!
—End of argument.

238
00:17:48,291 --> 00:17:50,703
You want to end up like that man?
Forgotten?

